<html>
<head>
    <title>JavaScript Basics</title>
</head>
<body>
<h1>Introduction to JavaScript</h1>

<h2>The Script Tag</h2>

<p>JavaScript code in HTML is contained within <script> tags as shown:</p>

<pre>
&lt;script&gt;
    document.getElementById("example").innerHTML = "JavaScript Sample";
&lt;/script&gt;
</pre>

<h2>JavaScript Functions and User Events</h2>

<p>A JavaScript function is a chunk of code that executes on call, such as when a user clicks a button.</p>

<h2>Position of JavaScript</h2>

<p>JavaScript code can be embedded in either the <head> or the <body> section of an HTML page or both.</p>

<h3>JavaScript in Head</h3>

<p>Example to illustrate JavaScript in the head section:</p>

<pre>
&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;
&lt;html&gt;
&lt;head&gt;
&lt;script&gt;
function mySampleFunction() {
    document.getElementById("example").innerHTML = "Content Updated.";
}
&lt;/script&gt;
&lt;/head&gt;
&lt;body&gt;
    &lt;h2&gt;JavaScript in Head Demo&lt;/h2&gt;
    &lt;p id="example"&gt;A Sample Paragraph&lt;/p&gt;
    &lt;button type="button" onclick="mySampleFunction()"&gt;Run Script&lt;/button&gt;
&lt;/body&gt;
&lt;/html&gt;
</pre>

<h3>JavaScript in Body</h3>

<p>Example to illustrate JavaScript in the body section:</p>

<pre>
&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;
&lt;html&gt;
&lt;body&gt;
    &lt;h2&gt;JavaScript in Body Demo&lt;/h2&gt;
    &lt;p id="example"&gt;A Sample Paragraph&lt;/p&gt;
    &lt;button type="button" onclick="myFunction()"&gt;Run Script&lt;/button&gt;
    &lt;script&gt;
        function myFunction() {
            document.getElementById("example").innerHTML = "Content Updated.";
        }
    &lt;/script&gt;
&lt;/body&gt;
&lt;/html&gt;
</pre>

<p>Placing scripts at the bottom of the body element can enhance the display speed.</p>

<h2>External JavaScript Files</h2>

<p>Scripts can also be stored in external files with .js extension. Example of an external file: myScript.js</p>

<pre>
function myFunction() {
   document.getElementById("example").innerHTML = "Content Updated.";
}
</pre>

<p>To use an external script, link to it via the src (source) attribute of a script tag:</p>

<pre>
&lt;script src="myScript.js"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;
</pre>

<p>The positioning of the script tag determines the location of the external script.</p>

<h3>Advantages of External JavaScript</h3>

<ul>
    <li>Helps separate HTML and JavaScript code, enhancing readability and maintainability.</li>
    <li>Speeds up page load times with cached JavaScript files.</li>
</ul>

<p>For multiple scripts, use several script tags:</p>

<pre>
&lt;script src="myScript1.js"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;
&lt;script src="myScript2.js"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;
</pre>

<h3>External Script References</h3>

<p>An external script can be referenced in 3 different ways:</p>

<ul>
    <li>With a full URL <pre>&lt;script src="http://yourwebsite.com/js/myScript.js"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;</pre></li>
    <li>With a file path <pre>&lt;script src="/js/myScript.js"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;</pre></li>
    <li>Without any path <pre>&lt;script src="myScript.js"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;</pre></li>
</ul>

</body>
</html>